It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper mentions the use of DNNs such as LeNet-5, AlexNet, and VGGNet, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with DNNs and their optimization. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as DNNs are a popular tool in the field of AI. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper involves optimization techniques and deals with the reduction of data storage.
